            "answer": "Afrinet Capital's official website is not listed; its LinkedIn page connects African entrepreneurs to global investors. Afrinet Holdings operates in multiple sectors, including IT and communications.\nAfrinet Capital LLC connects African entrepreneurs to global investors; founded in 2015, it operates in financial services with 2-10 employees. Afrinet Global focuses on financial services and digital transformation in Africa, employing 201-500 staff.\nAfrinet Capital is a venture advisory firm founded in 2015, connecting African entrepreneurs to global investors. It focuses on financial services and has 2-10 employees. Crunchbase data indicates ongoing venture funding trends for diverse startups.\nWellfound is a hiring platform for startups, spun out of AngelList, offering a free self-serve talent pipeline. Afrinet Capital is a venture capital firm with investments in companies like World Education Services and Bidhaa Sasa. Wellfound's AI tool assists in recruiting by sourcing candidates and suggesting next steps.\nAfrinet Capital Dealroom raised $7M in funding led by Índico Capital Partners, with participation from existing investors. The platform connects African startups with investors and facilitates deal-making. The latest funding will enhance Dealroom's data and AI capabilities.",
